  "prompt": "How can I play DLC on PS4 disc based games?",
  "response": "To play DLC (Downloadable Content) on PS4 disc-based games, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Ensure You Have the Base Game**: You must have the physical disc of the game that the DLC is for. The DLC will only work with the corresponding base game.\n\n2. **Purchase and Download DLC**: \n   - Go to the PlayStation Store, either through your PS4 or through the PlayStation website.\n   - Search for the DLC you want to purchase.\n   - Make sure the DLC is compatible with your disc-based game. Purchase and download it.\n\n3. **Install the DLC**: \n   - If you've purchased the DLC from the PlayStation Store, it should automatically start downloading and installing.\n   - If you have a code for the DLC (e.g., from a physical purchase), go to the main menu, select \"PlayStation Store,\" then \"Redeem Codes\" to enter the code and start the download.\n\n4. **Insert the Game Disc**: The game disc must be in your PS4 for the DLC to work. This confirms you own the base game.\n\n5. **Launch the Game**: Start your game from the home screen. The game should recognize the downloaded DLC and allow you to access the new content in-game. \n\n6. **Check for Updates**: Sometimes, you may need additional updates for the base game or the DLC to function properly. Make sure both the game and your console are updated to the latest software.\n\n7. **Access DLC Content**: Depending on the game, the method to access the DLC content can vary. It might be included in the main menu, available through in-game menus, or integrated into specific gameplay moments.\n\nIf you follow these steps and still encounter issues accessing DLC content, ensure that your console is properly connected to the internet and check for any known issues or FAQs related to that specific game.",
